               <msContents>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_111554">Swarby</placeName>. Indented demise by William Durem of Walkot' to Isabel daughter of John atte Grene of Walkot' in Swarrby, for the term of her life, of the third part of a messuage with croft in the vill of Swarrby which Sedonia Typpyng once held as dower, for an annual rent of 2s. at the four usual terms, and appearance (adventus) at his court at Swarrby next after Michaelmas. Isabel is to maintain the houses in the said third part. (Witnesses given.) At Swarrby. <origDate when="1320-07-06">Sunday after the translation of St Thomas Martyr, 13 Edw. II (6 July 1320)</origDate>. Seal lost.</p>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <history>
